cyclone.name: ETA
cyclone.current_location: about 45 miles NNW of Key West, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: moving west-northwest into the southeast Gulf of Mexico, then forecast to slow, turn north, and approach the Florida Gulf Coast late week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Gulf Coast between Tampa Bay and the Big Bend

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch in effect for parts of western Cuba (La Habana westward)
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning for the northwestern Bahamas, the Florida Keys, Florida Bay, and the Florida coast from the Brevard/Volusia County line southward on the east coast and northward to Anna Maria Island on the west coast
weather_observation.impacted_coast: South Florida, Florida Keys, Florida west coast, northwestern Bahamas
weather_observation.wind: Low chance (≤10%) of sustained tropical-storm-force winds late in the work-week; brief gusts possible if outer rainbands reach the Georgia coast.
weather_observation.storm_surge: No significant storm-surge inundation forecast for coastal Georgia under the current track.
weather_observation.rainfall: Outer rainbands could bring 1–3 inches of rain Friday into Saturday.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Isolated tornado threat cannot be ruled out in any rainbands that reach coastal Georgia late week.
